First Bank of Nigeria Limited has said the financial institution, as a responsible organisation has built trust on the pillar of security and safety for over 125 years and is committed to continuous improvement. The bank in a press statement said continuous improvement for the bank involves taking learnings even from unfortunate situations to further strengthen its security protocols. The bank’s statement, signed by the group head, Marketing and Corporate Communications, Folake Ani-Mumuney, was in reaction to the ongoing investigations by the police on foiled attempt by a gang of robbers to rob a branch of the bank at Mpape area of Abuja, last weekend. ‘‘We are aware that a customer service executive assigned to us by one of our vendors is helping the police with their investigations into the attempted robbery that happened last week in one of our branches in Abuja. ‘‘We remain grateful that none of our staff or customers lost their lives during the incident. We will however refrain from commenting further at this time until the relevant authorities conclude their investigations and we urge all to cooperate fully to enable seamless investigations,’’ the statement read in part. Three members of the gang were arrested last week after they were trapped in the bank by security agents. One was shot dead while trying to escape. A team of police officers and soldiers had laid siege to the bank, scuttling the operation.